SIMPLE: repugnancy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Repugnancy
<hw>Re*pug"nan*cy</hw> <pr>(-n<it>a</it>n-s?)</pr>, }</mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>r⟦eacute⟧pugnance</ets>, L.
<ets>repugnantia</ets>.]</ety> <def>The state or condition of being
repugnant; opposition; contrariety; especially, a strong instinctive
antagonism; aversion; reluctance; unwillingness, as of mind, passions,
principles, qualities, and the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That which causes us to lose most of our time is the
<qex>repugnance</qex> which we naturally have to labor.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let the foes quietly cut their throats,⟦br⟧
Without <qex>repugnancy</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Aversion; reluctance; unwillingness; dislike;
antipathy; hatred; hostility; irreconcilableness; contrariety;
inconsistency. See <er>Dislike</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repugnant</ent>⟦br⟧
